# Tags System for Notes - Implementation Plan

**Date:** 2025-11-26
**Status:** 🔵 PLANNING
**Priority:** P2 - MEDIUM (Priority #4)
**Estimated Time:** 2-3 hours

---

## Overview

Implement a comprehensive tagging system for notes, inspired by Obsidian, Roam Research, and Notion. Users can tag notes with hashtags (#work, #personal, #ideas), filter by tags, and organize their knowledge base with flexible categorization.

**User Problem:**
Users building a knowledge base with Daily Notes and regular notes need a flexible way to categorize and find related content. Folders alone are too rigid - a note about "#work #meeting #project-x" belongs in multiple conceptual categories.

**Technical Problem:**
Notes currently support tags as an array of strings, but there's no UI for managing tags, no tag autocomplete, no filtering by tags, and no tag overview/statistics. We need to build a complete tag management experience.

---

## Problem Statement

**Current behavior:**
- Notes have a `tags: string[]` field in the data model
- No UI to add/remove/manage tags
- No tag picker or autocomplete
- No way to filter notes by tags
- No tag overview or statistics
- Tags are just stored data with no functionality

**Desired behavior:**
- Click to add tags to any note (inline tag picker)
- Tag autocomplete from existing tags
- Filter notes by one or more tags
- Tag overview showing all tags + note counts
- Click tag to filter notes
- Tag renaming (renames across all notes)
- Tag deletion (removes from all notes)
- Tag colors/styling for visual distinction

**User impact:**
- **High** for power users organizing large knowledge bases
- **Medium** for daily notes users wanting to categorize entries
- **Core feature** in Obsidian, Roam, Notion - competitive parity

