## Design Considerations

### Design System Compliance
- **Colors:** Tag chips use `bg-accent-purple/10 text-accent-purple` (matches existing tag styling in widgets)
- **Components:** Use bento-card for TagManager modal
- **Typography:** `text-sm` for tags, `text-xs` for counts
- **Spacing:** `gap-2` between tags, `p-2` padding in chips
- **Animations:** Framer Motion for modal, subtle hover effects on tags
- **Dark Mode:** Auto-handled by semantic tokens

### Tag Display Patterns
**Option 1: Below Title (Recommended)**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Note Title                       │
│ ─────────────────────────────── │
│ #work #meeting #project-x [+]   │  ← Tags here
│ ─────────────────────────────── │
│ Note content starts here...     │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Option 2: In Title Bar**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│ Note Title    #work #meeting [+]│  ← Tags inline
│ ─────────────────────────────── │
│ Note content starts here...     │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Decision:** Use Option 1 (below title) - cleaner separation, more space for tags

### Tag Filtering Logic
- **AND logic:** Notes must have ALL selected tags
- Example: Filter by `#work` AND `#meeting` → only notes with both tags
- Clear visual indication of active filters
- Easy to add/remove filters

### Performance
- **Bundle Size Impact:** ~2-3KB (small components)
- **Lazy Loading:** No lazy loading needed (core feature)
- **Optimization:** Memoize tag counts, filter only when tags change

### Accessibility
- **Keyboard Nav:** Tab through tags, Enter to select, Escape to close
- **Screen Reader:** `role="button"` on tags, `aria-label="Add tag to note"`
- **Focus Management:** Focus returns to "Add tag" button after closing picker

